A lighthouse to the south mirrored a guard tower. The former’s purpose was to welcome things in. The latter was to keep things out. 

The night before, I was planning to bring something out.

----

We </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/07/dispatch-from-tijuana-cookie-aisle.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-6850964415187143927</guid><pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2011 09:55:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-07-07T02:55:46.829-07:00</atom:updated><title>Free(d) Ai Weiwei</title><atom:summary type='text'>Yesterday, people were protesting in front of the S-Bahn. They had tape on their mouths and demanded the release of Ai Weiwei, even though he was freed from a Beijing jail three weeks ago. The protest continued because they still had it marked on their calendars. German efficiency.</atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/07/freed-ai-weiwei.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-5658936719965478823</guid><pubDate>Tue, 05 Jul 2011 14:15:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-07-07T02:56:16.150-07:00</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>uk</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Travel</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>travel writing</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>London</category><title>London in the Spring of '11 (demo tape)</title><atom:summary type='text'>I’d only been in the country for three hours, and I spend $100. I’m gouged by our dollar’s relative worthlessness, my inability to calculate simple equations in my head, and not booking bus tickets weeks in advance. But I’m here now and that’s what matters. I have a few thousand dollars that I saved from unemployment checks that’ll need to last the whole summer. But hell, a 6.5% beer only costs </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/07/london-in-spring-of-11-demo.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-2083945501069476595</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jun 2011 11:57:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-06-14T04:57:25.064-07:00</atom:updated><title>Vama Veche</title><atom:summary type='text'>At the bus station a Gypsy wearing a bright colored yellow Armani sparkling t-shirt begged for change. I bought some food and water, before we had to jump on the next bus. I handed pieces of a meat filled pastry to my sister as a middle aged woman with a band-aid on her right arm made plans to pick up bread at the local “bucaterie.” Her telephone had different ringtones for different people. One </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/06/vama-veche.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-4775735737895656232</guid><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jun 2011 11:48:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-06-14T04:48:30.137-07:00</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>constanta</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>romania</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Travel</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>travel writing</category><title>Romanian Port on the Black Sea</title><atom:summary type='text'>We got in at 2:15 AM.  A driver said he’d take us to the hostel for “2.” He put up two fingers. Forgetting the Romanian exchange rate this seemed like a good deal. I showed him where we were going on the map. He drove around the block five times. He wasn’t actually a cab driver, we were in his family station wagon.

