We find a cab and attempt communication. "We are going to the youth hostel." He doesn't seem to understand, but somehow drops us off where we are </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/06/chisinau.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-8877443860189533746</guid><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jun 2011 15:23:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-06-07T08:23:28.241-07:00</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Travel</category><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>travel writing</category><title>Brasov to Chisinau</title><atom:summary type='text'>I hand my passport to a teenage ticket agent who remembered me. He brought me aboard the Chisinau-bound bus. I bought my ticket from a guy with a shaved head wearing a wolf t-shirt.

