The walls of the old mansion are covered with lyrics from the 1997 Baz Luhrmann song "Everybody's Free (To Wear </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/05/bucuresti.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-1229978854540542114</guid><pubDate>Tue, 24 May 2011 15:14:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-05-24T08:27:33.850-07:00</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Travel</category><title>Luton - Baneasa</title><atom:summary type='text'>I handed the bus driver all of my money. You can't get on the 22:38 bus with a 10:38 ticket. I should have researched international timing conventions. I blew fifty dollars instantly.

My sister's fountain pen wouldn't work. I tried creating a vacuum with my mouth. The ink blackened my teeth. Again I felt like an idiot.

