It’s okay to be an asshole sometimes. I think it's important to consider because assholes are often people with an overconfidence. Being thoroughly confident is what a good artist </atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/05/its-okay-to-be-asshole-sometimes.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item><item><guid isPermaLink='false'>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-11929692.post-7816577869989759709</guid><pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2011 20:09:00 +0000</pubDate><atom:updated>2011-05-09T13:11:09.610-07:00</atom:updated><category domain='http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#'>Art</category><title>Un-tragic Art</title><atom:summary type='text'>There's a history of the tortured artist. A new precedent is being set by artists who aren’t "fucked up." Artists, without tragic biographies need to trailblaze new descriptions of the artist. We can make a living making art without thinking we need to be poor or suicidal.</atom:summary><link>http://hellerscorner.blogspot.com/2011/05/un-tragic-art.html</link><author>joshuaheller@gmail.com (Heller)</author><thr:total>0</thr:total></item></channel></rss>